---
pagination:
  data: states.list
  size: 1
  alias: state
permalink: "/legal/{{ state.slug }}/"
layout: layouts/page.njk
eleventyComputed:
  title: "Legal Help in {{ state.name }}"
  heading: "Legal help in {{ state.name }}."
  eyebrow: "Legal · {{ state.name }}"
  section: "Legal"
  sectionUrl: "/legal/"
  lead: "Custody, child support, and legal aid are run at the state level — here's how to reach {{ state.name }}'s official resources."
  description: "Official child support and legal aid resources for single fathers in {{ state.name }}: how to find your local office and free legal help."
---
        <p>The rules for custody, child support, and legal aid are set and run by <strong>{{ state.name }}</strong>, not by any national office. So the most useful thing we can do is send you straight to the official {{ state.name }} doors. These trusted federal and nonprofit directories route you to the right place in your state:</p>

        <div class="cards">
          <article class="card">
            <span class="card-num">Child Support</span>
            <h3>{{ state.name }} child support agency</h3>
            <p>Open a case, make or receive payments, or get help with an existing order through {{ state.name }}'s official child support agency.</p>
            <ul class="card-links">
              <li><a href="{{ state.childSupportUrl or 'https://acf.gov/css/parents/find-local-child-support-office' }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">{{ state.name }} child support &rarr;</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://acf.gov/css/parents/find-local-child-support-office" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Find a local office (federal locator) &rarr;</a></li>
            </ul>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <span class="card-num">Legal Aid</span>
            <h3>Free &amp; low-cost legal help in {{ state.name }}</h3>
            <p>Find nonprofit legal aid you may qualify for, plus self-help resources, through these national finders.</p>
            <ul class="card-links">
              <li><a href="https://www.lsc.gov/about-lsc/what-legal-aid/i-need-legal-help" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LSC legal aid finder →</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://www.lawhelp.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LawHelp.org →</a></li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </div>

        <div class="callout">
          <p><strong>New to all this?</strong> Start with the plain-English basics that apply everywhere, then use the {{ state.name }} links above for the specifics: <a href="{{ '/legal/custody/' | url }}">Custody &amp; Visitation</a>, <a href="{{ '/legal/child-support/' | url }}">Child Support</a>, and <a href="{{ '/legal/finding-legal-help/' | url }}">Finding Legal Help</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <p class="page-foot-note">Looking for a different state? <a href="{{ '/legal/' | url }}">Pick your state on the Legal page</a>.</p>
